                                    7.1 To remain active on the Website and continue to receive Donations paid to it through the Website from SAANA, Nonprofits must comply with the following requirements:

                                    <br><br> (a) Reporting Requirements: The Nonprofit must submit quarterly project reports to SAANA, Inc which provide an update to both the Nonprofit’s supporters and SAANA, Inc's staff on the project’s progress (“Quarterly Project Reports”). The first Quarterly Project Report should be provided within 90 days of the Nonprofit posting a project on the Website, regardless of whether it has received any funding. The Quarterly Project Reports will be made visible on the Website and sent to relevant Donors and email subscribers. The Nonprofit must also provide a final written report to SAANA, Inc upon its project being marked as ‘fully funded’ on the Website.

                                    <br><br> (b) Due Diligence Requirements: The Due Diligence Process conducted by SAANA, Inc at the time of a Nonprofit’s registration shall, unless otherwise specified by SAANA, Inc, expire two years after the completion of such due diligence. Upon such expiry and at a minimum every two years thereafter, SAANA, Inc will undertake any further checks it deems necessary to re-verify the identity and objectives of such Nonprofit. If a Nonprofit fails to provide SAANA, Inc with the additional documentation required for SAANA, Inc to complete such follow-up due diligence, SAANA, Inc will deactivate all projects relating to the Nonprofit that are listed on the Website and the Nonprofit will not be allowed to participate in any SAANA, Inc affiliate programs. SAANA, Inc reserves the right to require any organization to submit documentation to SAANA, Inc at any time to verify the use of funds, confirm programmatic activity, or for other Due Diligence purposes. If the Nonprofit has pending Donations which need to be disbursed, SAANA, Inc will within 30 days of the expiration of the previous due diligence, make its final payment to such Nonprofit.

                                    <br><br> (c) Miscellaneous Requests: The Nonprofit must comply with any document requests made by SAANA, Inc at any time to verify the use of funds, confirm programmatic activity, or for other due diligence purposes; and

                                    <br><br> (d) Records Retention: The Nonprofit must maintain records of all receipts and expenditures of received grants and donations for a period of at least seven years after such grants and donations have been expended.

